body:
@Fokko I'm not fond of it either, and I'm definitely not attached to it by any means. My goal was to get the system working and then start the conversation of how to productionize it.

The `run --local` was working before, but unfortunately something in the last month of commits has broken it and now when I attempt to run it it seems to fail silently (like I'm getting failures in the DB but there's no failures/errors reported in the logs).

Would having `airflow run --kubernetes-mode` be better, or should we strive to have the workers work completely within the existing airflow functionality?
